              <div class="card-body">
                <h6 class="mb-3"><strong>Services</strong></h6>
                <dl class="mb-0">
                  <dt>Caddy</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">Web server and reverse proxy. Handles HTTP/HTTPS routing, SSL certificates, and forwards requests to PHP-FPM.</dd>
                  <dt>MySQL</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">Relational database storing all Tribe content and application data.</dd>
                  <dt>Typesense</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">Fast search engine by <a href="https://typesense.org" target="_blank">typesense.org</a>. Indexes Tribe content for full-text search.</dd>
                  <dt>phpMyAdmin</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">Web UI for browsing and managing MySQL databases.</dd>
                  <dt>FileBrowser</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-0">Web UI for browsing and managing uploaded files by <a href="https://filebrowser.org" target="_blank">filebrowser.org</a>.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card method-item h-100">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h6 class="mb-3"><strong>Developer Tools</strong></h6>
                <dl class="mb-0">
                  <dt>Composer</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">PHP dependency manager. Used to install <code>tribe-core</code> and any other PHP packages. Runs once per project (or once per Loom setup).</dd>
                  <dt>npm</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">Node Package Manager. Used to install <code>ember-tribe</code> and all frontend JavaScript dependencies.</dd>
                  <dt>Node.js</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">JavaScript runtime required for Ember CLI tooling. Install via NVM; Tribe requires the latest LTS version.</dd>
                  <dt>Ember CLI</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-0">Command-line tool for creating, building and serving EmberJS applications. Install globally with <code>npm install -g ember-cli</code>.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card method-item h-100">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h6 class="mb-3"><strong>Loom (Multi Tribe)</strong></h6>
                <dl class="mb-0">
                  <dt>Loom</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">Multi Tribe hosting mode. One shared set of services (MySQL, Typesense, Caddy) supports many isolated Threads.</dd>
                  <dt>Thread</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-0">A single Tribe + Junction instance within a Loom setup. Has its own database, uploads folder and port pair. App code is shared read-only.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-md-6">
            <div class="card method-item h-100">
              <div class="card-body">
                <h6 class="mb-3"><strong>Tor (Onion Services)</strong></h6>
                <dl class="mb-0">
                  <dt>Tor</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-2">Overlay mode that routes all traffic through <code>.onion</code> services. No host ports are exposed. Works with single-project Tribe only.</dd>
                  <dt>.onion address</dt>
                  <dd class="text-muted small mb-0">A v3 hidden service address (56 chars, ed25519). Derived from a private key stored in <code>uploads/tor/</code>. Permanent as long as the key is preserved.</dd>
                </dl>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
